01/04/2021,748.2203(c) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,03/18/2021,03/22/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,There was a medication error documented for a child in care. There was no follow-up completed for this error to include all requirements as per 748.2203(c)(1-5).,"Corrective Action Plan
Investigation: 2690611
Standards to Address:
§748.2203(c) No follow up completed for medication error.
Action to be taken:
For healthcare appointments, the assigned case manager and medical coordinator will assess within 72 hours of intake to ensure proper scheduling and attendance of appointment, documentation will be reconciled and reviewed daily. Any follow-ups or reschedules will be completed with in 48 business hours.
Completed healthcare appointment paperwork will be uploaded into the client management system and filed in the clients file with in 15 days.
Seton Home provided retraining for domestic direct care staff and case managers on 1/7/2021
Seton Home will be conducting weekly audits on all behavioral health assessments/appointments related to medications to ensure compliance."
